org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.utility

Interface Preconditions


  • public interface Preconditions
    Interface contains precondition methods to validity reference object(s) as one-liner.

    agatting on 14.09.17.

      • checkNotNull

        static <T> T checkNotNull(T reference,
                          String errorMessage)
                   throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method ensures that an object reference passed as a parameter to the calling method is not null.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the data type of the reference object.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the object, which should be checked.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        Returns:
        the non-null reference that was validated.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the parameter is null.

      • checkNotNull

        static org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack checkNotNull(Object reference,
                                                                             Object source,
                                                                             String errorMessage,
                                                                             org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack)
        Method ensures that an object reference passed as a parameter to the calling method is not null. Possible NotAvailableException is stacked and returned.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the object, which should be checked.
        source - is the source of the reference. Can be ignored by NULL.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        exceptionStack - is used to bundle possible exception. If NULL a new exceptionStack will be created.
        Returns:
        the exceptionStack with an following entry if the check fails. Otherwise input stack is returned.

      • multipleCheckNotNull

        static org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack multipleCheckNotNull(Object source,
                                                                                     org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack,
                                                                                     Object... objects)
        Method ensures that one or multiple object reference(s) passed as a parameter to the calling method is/are not null. Possible NotAvailableException is stacked and returned. By using one object reference use the single version method to be able to specify the content if exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        source - is the source of the reference(s). Can be ignored by NULL.
        exceptionStack - is used to bundle possible exception. If NULL a new exceptionStack will be created.
        objects - are the reference objects, which should be checked.
        Returns:
        the exceptionStack with or without new exception entry.

      • multipleCheckNotNullAndThrow

        static void multipleCheckNotNullAndThrow(Object source,
                                         Object... objects)
                                  throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException
        Method ensures that one or multiple object reference(s) passed as a parameter to the calling method is/are not null. Throws Exception otherwise.
        Parameters:
        source - is the source of the reference(s). Can be ignored by NULL.
        objects - are the reference parameter, which should be checked.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case at least one reference parameter is NULL.

      • callFunction

        static <T,R> R callFunction(Function<T,R> function,
                            T functionArgument,
                            Object source,
                            org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack)
        Method executes the input function (needs exactly one argument) and returns the result. If the input function provokes an exception (cause e.g. wrong parameter), it will be stacked on the input exceptionStack and NULL will be returned. Check the exceptionStack in this case.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the type of the argument to the function.
        R - is the type of the result to the function.
        Parameters:
        function - represents a function with one argument and produces an result.
        functionArgument - is the single argument of the function.
        source - is the source of the function. Can be ignored by NULL.
        exceptionStack - is used to bundle possible exception. If NULL a new exceptionStack will be created.
        Returns:
        the result of the function with type R. Returns null if an exception occurs. Check exceptionStack.

      • callBiFunction

        static <T,U,R> R callBiFunction(BiFunction<T,U,R> function,
                                T functionArgOne,
                                U functionArgTwo,
                                Object source,
                                org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack)
        Method executes the input function (needs exactly two arguments) and returns the result. If the input function provokes an exception (cause e.g. wrong parameter), it will be stacked on the input exceptionStack and NULL will be returned. Check the exceptionStack in this case.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the type of the first argument to the function.
        U - is the type of the second argument to the function.
        R - is the type of the result to the function.
        Parameters:
        function - represents a function with one argument and produces an result.
        functionArgOne - is the first argument of the function.
        functionArgTwo - is the second argument of the function.
        source - is the source of the function. Can be ignored by NULL.
        exceptionStack - is used to bundle possible exception. If NULL a new exceptionStack will be created.
        Returns:
        the result of the function with type R. Returns null if an exception occurs. Check exceptionStack.

      • callSupplier

        static <R> R callSupplier(Supplier<R> function,
                          Object source,
                          org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack)
        Method executes the input function without argument and returns the result. If the input function provokes an exception it will be stacked on the input exceptionStack object and NULL will be returned. Check the exceptionStack in this case.
        Type Parameters:
        R - is the type of the result to the function.
        Parameters:
        function - represents a function without any argument and produces an result.
        source - of the function. Can be ignored by NULL.
        exceptionStack - is used to bundle possible exception. If NULL a new exceptionStack will be created.
        Returns:
        the result of the function with type R. Returns null if an exception occurs. Check exceptionStack.

      • callSupplier

                   throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException

        Type Parameters:
        R - is the type of the result to the function.
        Parameters:
        function - represents a function without any argument and produces an result.
        Returns:
        the result of the function with type R.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the function throws an exception.

      • checkHasContent

        static String checkHasContent(String reference,
                              String errorMessage)
                       throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method ensures that an string reference passed as a parameter to the calling method is not null or empty. The reference will be returned if it has content. Otherwise an exception is thrown if NULL or empty.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the string, which should be checked.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        Returns:
        the input reference if it isn't empty.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the reference is null or empty.

      • initializeIfNull

        Method initializes the input exceptionStack if it's null.
        Parameters:
        exceptionStack - which should be initialized.
        Returns:
        an initialized and empty exceptionStack if input is null. Otherwise the unchanged input exceptionStack.
